items.title: Israeli strike on Gaza seafront cafe kills at least 20 Palestinians, witnesses and rescuers say
items.description: The outdoor cafe was frequently used by journalists, activists and local residents.

items.title: 'Unprecedented' alerts in France as blistering heat grips Europe
items.description: Dozens of the country's mainland regions are currently under the second-highest alert as the heatwave continues.

items.title: Key witness in ex-Peru mayor's corruption case found dead
items.description: José Miguel Castro was collaborating with prosecutors in the corruption case against Susana Villarán.

items.title: 'A little bit melting': Intense heat across Europe
items.description: A new heat record for June of 46C was set in Spain this weekend as Europe experiences an intense heatwave.

items.title: US must rule out more strikes before new talks, Iranian minister tells BBC
items.description: Majid Takht-Ravanchi said the Trump administration has "not made their position clear" on further attacks.
